      "content": "but \"fleeting moments\" are just temporary distractions from the inevitable. it's exhausting to keep fighting against the tide. if nothing truly matters and the darkness is the only thing that's real, then maybe the struggle itself is just unnecessary. if the void is what's actually true, why should i keep pretending otherwise?",
